<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian IOC member Siperco Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Alexandru Siperco, who had
served on te IOC for 43 years and the longest-serving member on
the International Olypmic Committee, died on Monday. He was 77.
</P>
<P>
Siperco had been elected as the member of the IOC in 1955, di
ed at his Bucharest home of a heart attack, according to the
Romanian Olympic Committee.
</P>
<P>
Crin Antonescu, Romania's Minister of Sport and Youth, who met
with Siperco three weeks ago, said: "It's a great loss and his
life was dedicated to the International Olympic Committee."
</P>
<P>
Siperco, born in Tataresti in 1920, was president of the
Romanian Olympic Committee from 1952 to 1959.
</P>
<P>
He was an IOC executive board member from 1979 to 1986, and
IOC vice president from 1982 to 1986.
</P>
<P>
Siperco became the ``doyen'' of the IOC when the Grand Duke of
Luxembourg, who had served on the IOC since 1946, resigned
earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Siperco, who is survived by his wife and five children, would
have turned 78 on Nov. 5.
</P>
<P>
IOC president Juan Antonio Samaranch, who is expected to
attend Siperco's funeral Wednesday, sent a letter of condolence
to Siperco's family, saying, ``We shall all remember Mr. Siperco
for his distinguished service to the Olympic family.''
</P>
<P>
Siperco is the second IOC member to die in the past 10 days.
Spain's Carlos Ferrer Salat, president of the Spanish Olympic
Committee, died October 18 in Barcelona of a heart attack.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
