<HEADLINE> Belarus Donates for Chinese Flood-Ravaged Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 27 (Xinhua) --The Republic of Belarus today
donated 36 tons of disaster-relief materials valued at over one
million yuan (120,000 US dollars) to flood-ravaged areas in
central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The materials, mainly medicine and food, arrived at the
international airport of Tianjin Municipality this morning.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yuxiu, an official with the Ministry of Civil Affairs,
expressed thanks to the Belarus government and people. Zhang said
that many foreign countries and international organizations have
donated cashes and materials to China's natural disaster-ravaged
areas.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will use the donation to help victims in
the areas rebuild their homes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
