<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina's Menem Arrives in UK for Landmark Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos Menem
arrived in Britain on Tuesday for a six-day official visit which
is expected to repair bilateral ties alienated by the 1982
Falklands War between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Menem's entourage includes several government ministers and
leading business executives. During the visit, the first by an
Argentine leader since 1960, Menem will hold talks with Prime
Minister Tony Blair and Queen Elizabeth, meet British investors
and give a major speech on Anglo-Argentine relations, according to
Reuters.
</P>
<P>
Also, he will lay a wreath at the memorial to Britain's
Falklands dead in St Paul's Cathedral.
</P>
<P>
Argentina claims sovereignty over the British-ruled South
Atlantic islands, which it refers to as the Malvinas. But Britain
has repeatedly insisted there will be no negotiations on
sovereignty during the visit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
