<HEADLINE> Soros To Shut Down Hedge Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 27 (Xinhua) -- George Soros, one of the
world's most famous investors, plans to shut down his 1.5 billion
U.S. dollars emerging market hedge fund and make some changes at
his Quantum Group of mutual funds after poor investment returns in
the recent months of global financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Some of Soros' funds have showed declines of more than 15
percent so far this year and the Quantum Emerging Growth Fund
Soros is proposing to close has dropped in value by 31 percent for
the year through last Thursday, according to a spokesman for New
York-based Soros Fund Management.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to investors on Friday, Soros attributed the
decision to close the Quantum Emerging Growth Fund to "corporate
restructuring."  
</P>
</TEXT>
