<HEADLINE> Israeli Allied Militiaman Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 27 (Xinhua) -- A member of the Israeli allied
South Lebanon Army (SLA) was killed during a Lebanese guerrillas'
attack on Tuesday, the Orient radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The militiaman was killed when several shells fired by
guerrillas hit the SLA's post on the Hmayyed hill in the western
sector of the Israeli occupied south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, claimed
responsibility for the attack which raised to 28 the number of SLA
members killed in south Lebanon since the start of this year.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
cross-border attacks by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting trying to oust the Israeli forces and
its proxy SLA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
