<HEADLINE> IPE Welcomes Government's Consultation Paper On </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The International Petroleum
Exchange (IPE) Tuesday welcomed the government's consultation
paper on the UK Climate Change program released Monday.
</P>
<P>
The document clearly outlines the UK's international
responsibilities in reducing greenhouse gas emissions, and
confirms the government's commitment to playing an active role in
addressing the problems of climate change.
</P>
<P>
The paper states that there may be benefits in establishing a
domestic emissions trading scheme prior to the start up of an
international market.
</P>
<P>
The advantages listed include the more efficient and cost
effective achievement of emissions reductions in the UK and the
establishment of the City of London as a center for trading.
</P>
<P>
The IPE, Europe's leading energy futures and options exchange,
agrees that the UK should take the lead in setting up a market in
emissions.
</P>
<P>
Lynto Jones, chief executive of the IPE said: "the UK has a
great opportunity to set the agenda for the development of a
successful market in greenhouse gas emissions."
</P>
<P>
"We welcome the government's commitment to achieving major
reductions in emissions, and look forward to working closely with
them and with the business community to put these aims into
practice," he added.  
</P>
