<HEADLINE> PNA Urges Palestinians to Boycott Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Tuesday urged Palestinians to boycott the
elections for Jerusalem mayor, which will be hold by the Israeli
authorities next month.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of Israel Radio, Faisal Husseini, PNA
leading official in Jerusalem, told a news conference here that
the Palestinians' participation in the elections would signal
their acceptance of Israeli rule over the whole city.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Palestinian residents of the city should
stay at home during the elections, stressing that "We hope
they will not participate."
</P>
<P>
About 420,000 Jews and 180,000 Palestinians are living in
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
According to the peace agreement between Israel and PNA, the
Jerusalem issue will be determined in the final status talks
which have yet to begin.
</P>
<P>
Israel is insisting that it will never give up sovereignty
over the whole city, while the Palestinians want the east
Jerusalem, which Israel captured from Jordan in the 1967 Middle
East War, to be the capital of their future independent state.
</P>
<P>
The municipal elections of Jerusalem is due to begin on
November 10th and some 124,000 Palestinian residents of the city
are eligible to vote.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert, a hardliner in the ruling
Likud Party, is expected to be re-elected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
