<HEADLINE> Iran to Stage Largest Maneuver on Eastern Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced on Tuesday its
army would start the largest military maneuver since the end of
the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war, on the eastern border on October 31.
</P>
<P>
Commander of the army's ground force Brigadier General
Abdulali Pourshasb said the three armed services would take part
in the war games, codenamed "Zulfaqar 2," the official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver had been scheduled for September amid tensions
between Iran and Afghanistan triggered by the killing of nine
Iranian diplomats and reporter by the Afghan Taliban militia in
northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The army had earlier announced that 200,000 troops, which have
been deployed along the country eastern border with Afghanistan,
would be involved in the war games to show their combat
capabilities.
</P>
<P>
However, the maneuver was postponed after the United Nations
dispatched special envoy on Afghan affairs Lakhdar Brahimi to the
region to defuse the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi succeeded in persuading the Taliban, which now control
most of Afghanistan, to repatriate the remains of the killed
Iranians and release 51 Iranians captured in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
During the past month, the Iranian troops deployed in the
border areas carried out a series of military exercises in order
to be prepared for the main phase of the maneuver.
</P>
<P>
Pourshasb said that the army units stationed on eastern border
are on full alert, and the successful conduct of the war games is
indicative of the army's readiness to defend the entirety of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
