<HEADLINE> Forum Urges Rational Management of Water Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The third Mediterranean
Agricultural Forum on Tuesday emphasised the urgent need for a
rational and sustainable management of water resources in order to
guarantee their renewal.
</P>
<P>
A final joint statement said the two-day forum, whose theme was
the use of water in agriculture, called for preservation of water
in consideration of the increasing needs of water in the near
future.
</P>
<P>
The forum called for the introduction in each country of a
single water authority which, in cooperation with the World Water
Council, would contribute to achieving all the objectives brought
up during the meeting, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It added the forum examined the situation of water resources in
several Mediterranean countries and the legislations on the use of
water in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
It said the forum was satisfied with the participation, for the
first time, of parliamentarians from most Mediterranean countries
and from non-member countries of the European Council.
</P>
<P>
The forum was organized by the Committee of Agriculture and
Rural Development of the Parliamentary Assembly of the European
Council, in cooperation with the Mediterranean Committee of the
International Federation of Agricultural Producers and the
International Center for Advanced Mediterranean Agronomic Studies.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Egypt, Jordan, Albania, Israel, Morocco,
Ireland, Britain, Poland, France, Sweden, Italy, Spain, Tunisia,
the Czech Republic, Macedonia, Cyprus and the Palestinian National
Authority attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
