<HEADLINE> FTSE Eurotop 100's Fast Track To Frankfurt Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 27 (Xinhua) - Amsterdam Exchanges, FTSE
International and LIFFE, the European partners behind the FTSE
Eurotop 100 index and its futures and options, are launching a
major promotional campaign in Frankfurt during next two months.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 100 index, launched by AEX in 1990, is widely
accepted as an important European economic indicator for the most
actively traded stocks in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 100 campaign will emphasize the importance of
choosing an index that tracks Europe's markets closely, according
to an announcement Tuesday by LIFFE (The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange).
</P>
<P>
Tracking is an indication of how representative the index is
compared to the broader overall market. The better tracking
performance of the FTSE Eurotop 100 is due to its more
representative industry coverage and accurate country
representation.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the launch of the FTSE Eurotop 100 Campaign,
President of AEX, George Moller stated: "The FTSE Eurotop 100 is
designed in response to growing demand for trading against an
index of Europe's world class companies."
</P>
<P>
FTSE International manages and develops world-wide equity and
bond indices ranging from the FTSE 100 to the FT/S&AMP;P Actuaries
World Index.
</P>
<P>
Its indices are extensively used by fund managers world-wide
for investment analysis, performance measurement, asset allocation
and for creating a wide range of index-linked tracking funds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
