commercial rate of 59.7889 against one U.S. Dollar, unchanged
from Monday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said investors had put a wary eye on Kenya Breweries
ahead of annual financial results that analysts say will show a
decline in profits due to measures by the beer company to
rationalize its staff costs.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Breweries has also radically increased its advertizing
costs to better compete with South African Breweries, whose entry
into the eastern Africa market with its Castle brands has been
well received, observers said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, over-all profits of the Kenya Power &AMP; Lighting Co,
are in decline because of revenue collection problems. The firm
is owed millions of Shillings by government departments and
agencies despite a rise in the turnover. 
