<HEADLINE> S. Africa Hails Peru-Ecuador Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 27 (Xinhua) -- South Africa Tuesday
spoke highly of the peace accord signed by President Jamil Mahuad
of Ecuador and his Peruvian counterpart Alberto Fujimori in
Brasilia Monday.
</P>
<P>
The South African Department of Foreign Affairs said in a
statement that the accord would bring an end to over a century of
differences between the two countries over their common border.
</P>
<P>
