Truth and Reconciliation Commission final report Thursday and
return home Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He would be represented at the job summit by Deputy President
Thabo Mbeki.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said in a statement Tuesday that Mandela,
who has been invited to the summit by ECOWAS chairman Abdulsalam
Abubakar of Nigeria, would attend as an observer, and in his
capacity as chairman of the 14-member Southern African
Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
The ministry said it would afford Mandela an opportunity to
brief west African heads of state on a variety of SADC issues.
</P>
<P>
