<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2105GMT, October 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced on Tuesday its
army would start the largest military maneuver since the end of
the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war, on the eastern border on October 31.
</P>
<P>
Commander of the army's ground force Brigadier General
Abdulali Pourshasb said the three armed services would take part
in the war games, codenamed "Zulfaqar 2," the official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver had been scheduled for September amid tensions
between Iran and Afghanistan triggered by the killing of nine
Iranian diplomats and reporter by the Afghan Taliban militia in
northern Afghanistan. (BC-Iran-War Games-Taliban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu urged
the Israelis Tuesday to keep "cool heads", saying it is also a
criminal act to murder people for revenge, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
His remarks were made one day after a Jewish settler and a
Palestinian man were killed in two murders in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The body of the 68-year-old Palestinian, Mohammed Zalmout, was
found outside a Jewish settlement near Nablus Monday afternoon,
several hours after Danny Vargas, a 29-year-old Jewish settler in
Hebron was shot dead. (BC-Palestinian-Arrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
