Foreign Minister Ariel Sharon and Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai since they returned from the U.S. talks Sunday.
</P>
<P>
While continuing his effort to win approval for the agreement
by meeting with cabinet ministers, Netanyahu said Tuesday he
believes the opposition's move to hold early elections will not
succeed. (BC-Israel-Incitement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Four people were wounded by a car bomb blast in
Lebanon's southern biggest city of Sidon Tuesday morning, the
Orient radio reported.
</P>
<P>
At 9:05 a.m. (7:05 GMT), a huge sound was heard across the
city when the bomb in a car which was parked on Sidon's eastern
highway exploded.
</P>
<P>
Some Lebanese officials said the crime was aimed at
destabilizing the country during the presidential election in
which army commander Emile Lahoud was elected the next president
on October 15 by the parliament. (BC-Lebanon-Bomb Blast)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinian security forces announced Tuesday
afternoon that they have arrested two Palestinians suspected of
killing a Jewish settler in the divided West Bank town of Hebron
Monday, local television reported.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the two had confessed to the murder and also
the killing of another Israeli man in a communal farm outside
Jerusalem about two weeks ago. (BC-Palestinian-Arrest) 
