<HEADLINE> UK Government Welcomes NATO Decision on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The British government Tuesday
expressed its endorsement to a NATO decision to maintain its
threat of using force in Kosovo, Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
NATO announced early Tuesday that it would not launch air
strikes against Serbian targets for now but would maintain the
threat of military intervention against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said in a statement: "I
welcome NATO's decision to maintain its readiness to act. NATO has
not and will not lower its guard: the planes will stay on the
runway."
</P>
<P>
"(Yugoslav President Slobodan) Milosevic is at last making
serious progress toward compliance with UN Security Council
Resolutions. But this is only because of the continuing threat of
NATO action," Cook said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
"He (Milosevic) still has some way to go and there must be no
backsliding. So we shall remain vigilant, and keep the pressure on
him," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
