will take us to the next level," said U.S. Soccer President
Robert Contiguglia.
</P>
<P>
Arena won five NCAA titles at Virginia and two Major League
Soccer titles with D.C., and he earned favorable reviews for his
work with the 1996 U.S. Olympic team. Arena's contract is
estimated at 500,000 U.S. dollars a year for four years.
</P>
<P>
