40, coach of the MLS champion Chicago Fire, will serve as his
assistant.
</P>
<P>
"We need to rebuild with youth," Arena said. "I will not rule
out any players, but we want to be in a position to qualify in
the year 2000. I want to work closely with MLS coaches and
players to improve the vertical integration from top to bottom.
The pinnacle has to be the men's senior national team."
</P>
<P>
The USA team finished last among the 36 qualified teams in the
finals of the World Cup this summer. Arena acknowledges U.S.
soccer has work to do in restoring confidence.
</P>
<P>
"I think you will see a number of new faces that are young and
exciting," he said. "We're going to work with the media every
day, and I think we're going to try and give a little bit of
hope."
</P>
<P>
Sampson, Arena's predecessor, praised the selection: "A good
choice. For Bruce the most important thing is that he got a
four-year contract and he can work on getting those players
international experience."  
