<HEADLINE> Romania Hails Mideast Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Romania welcomes the interim
Israeli-Palestinian Peace Agreement signed in Washington on
October 23, a Romanian Foreign Ministry's spokeswoman said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Describing the accord as a success, spokeswoman Carmen
Podgoreanu said it was a result of the efforts of the two directly
involved parties as well as the international community. She
highlighted the role the United States played to restart peace
negotiations in the Middle East.
</P>
