<HEADLINE> Finland Increasing Forestry Cooperation With Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Governor Li Jiating of Yunnan
province, in a meeting with Finnish Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen
here this evening, said that there has been a good beginning for
Yunnan-Finnish cooperation and there should be more economic and
trade cooperation, especially in forestry.
</P>
<P>
He said that since 1995, the province has signed
telecommunications contracts with Finland worth 290 million U.S.
dollars and that more than half of the mobile telephones in the
province are Finnish products.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation for Finland's taking the lead in
deciding to take part in a world horticultural fair in Kunming
next year.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen voiced support for bilateral forestry cooperation and
for Finland's Forestry Minister's coming visit to the province and
said that by forestry he means both forest cultivation and
protection. He said that his country will cooperate with Yunnan in
related technology and personnel.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen arrived here this afternoon from Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
