<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's Manufacturing Output Slides in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's manufacturing
output in September 1998 fell by 1.7 per cent compared to the same
month last year with output of electronic and engineering clusters
shrinking and that of chemical cluster increasing gaining, the
country's Economic Development Board (EDB) said in a press release
Wednesday .
</P>
<P>
But the total cumulative output for the first nine months of
1998 grew by 0.2 per cent over the same period in 1997, it said.
</P>
<P>
According to the EDB, monthly output of the electronics and
engineering clusters declined by 4.8 and 6.3 per cent respectively
year-on-year while the output of the chemical cluster ran up 24.3
per cent over August 1997 with a hefty growth of 263 per cent in
the pharmaceuticals segment.
</P>
<P>
In regard of the accumulative output for the first nine months
1998, the electronics cluster registered a 3.5 per cent decline
than a year ago while chemicals and engineering clusters enjoyed
14.2 and 2.5 per cent growth respectively compared to September
1997, according to the EDB.  
</P>
</TEXT>
