<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Timely Implementation of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The United States is urging
Israel and the Palestinians to implement their new peace agreement
on time, Israel radio reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Larry Schwartz, spokesman of the U.S. Embassy in Tel Aviv, said
that "all sides must begin implementation next Monday night," the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Schwartz said U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright called
Palestinian National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat and Israeli
Foreign Minister Ariel Sharon earlier this week to push forward
the implementation of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
U.S. diplomats met on Wednesday with Palestinian officials to
prevent delays in the fulfillment of the agreement, he said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that
a cabinet meeting scheduled for Thursday to approve the agreement
was postponed indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu noted on Wednesday that the peace agreement would be
implemented only after his cabinet approved it.
</P>
<P>
"It happens to be that the prime minister cannot put forward
and cannot implement international treaties on his own," Netanyahu
said, adding "It has to be approved by the Cabinet."
</P>
<P>
Political sources told local daily Haaretz that Netanyahu
seems lacking a ministerial majority for approving the second
withdrawal of Israeli troops from the West Bank, as what was
agreed in the accord.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Arafat said on Wednesday that he was not
concerned about the postponing of the Israeli cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
"There are American guarantees, international guarantees and
Arab guarantees, " Arafat noted after returning to the Gaza Strip
from his Arab tour.
</P>
<P>
He stressed "I think that what has been signed will be
implemented accurately."
</P>
<P>
After nine-day talks, Arafat and Netanyahu signed last Friday
in Washington a land-for-peace agreement, under which Israel would
hand over 13 percent of the West Bank in the second redeployment
in return for the Palestinian's commitment to fight terrorism.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the two sides should start the
implementation of the deal next Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
