<HEADLINE> China To Strengthen Nature Reserves Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China will improve the
protection of nature reserves on the upper reaches of rivers to
restore the ecological balance in those areas.
</P>
<P>
According to a meeting on protection of nautral reserves in
northeast, north and northwest China, which was closed here today,
the action was intrigued by the serious flooding this year, which
was caused partly by soil erosion.
</P>
<P>
Northeast, north and northwest China are the source of almost
all of the rivers in the country. They have 191 natural reserves,
covering an area of 12.98 million hectares.
</P>
<P>
China has 926 natural reserves with a total area of
76.98 million hectares, accounting for 7.64 percent of the
country's total area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
