<HEADLINE> Corretja Beaten by Gambill in Eurocard Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Alex Corretja lost to
Jan-Michael Gambill 6-2, 6-4 in the second round of the 2.45
million dollar Eurocard Open in Stuggart, Germany, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Corretja, who has already qualified for next month's eight-man
ATP Tour World Championships in Hanover, Germany, was easily
handled by American Gambill, 50th in the world.
</P>
<P>
Gambill will play Briton Tim Henman, the ninth seed, in the
third round.
</P>
<P>
Last year's finalist Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands, the
No. 11, advanced easily over Swede Magnus Norman, 6-4, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Twelfth seed Jonas Bjorkman stumbled in the second set against
Italian veteran Gianluca Pozzi, but broke in the fifth game of
the third to re-establish winning momentum in their second-round
match.
</P>
<P>
The Swede claimed a 6-4, 3-6, 6-2 win after Pozzi saved three
match points in the final game on the way out. 
</P>
