<HEADLINE> Lightning Kills 11 Soccer Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZZAVILLE, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Eleven members of a
Congolese soccer team were killed by a burst of lightning and
dozens more people were injuried during a weekend match,
according to the Congolese news agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency reported Tuesday that the lightning strike wiped
out all the players fielded by the home team in the village of
Bena Tshadi, in the south-central Congolese province of Eastern
Kasai.
</P>
<P>
Local investigators are blaming the lightning bolt on
witchcraft because none of the players on the opposing team from
nearby Basangana village were injured, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The report added that sorcery is often used in the region in
an attempt to influence soccer games.
</P>
<P>
The two teams were tied 1-1 when the lightning struck.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 people, most standing along the sidelines, were
injured by the lightning, but none of the injuries are believed
to be life-threatening, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Witchcraft is often blamed throughout west and central Africa
to explain natural phenomenon and illness.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
