<HEADLINE> Second South Asian Architecture Awards Launched in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The South Asian Architecture
Awards for 1997 was launched here Wednesday with Nepal, Bhutan and
Bangladesh as the focus countries.
</P>
<P>
Initially an award for excellence in architecture, the
Architect of the Year Awards extended its scope from India to the
entire South Asian region in 1997 with a view to giving an impetus
to architecture in the region, the most populous area in the
world, for improvement of the surroundings and the quality of
life, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Every year one or more member countries of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) comprising
Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri
Lanka are invited to contest the awards as the focus countries.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka was the sole focus country invited last year for the
awards for 1996.
</P>
<P>
The second South Asian Architecture Awards are being jointly
organized by the Society of Nepalese Architects (SONA) and the
J.K. Cement Works in India.
</P>
<P>
"Architects -- firms, individuals from government as well as
the private sector are invited to send in their entries with
complete details about their projects concluded during the period
from January 1, 1995, to December 31, 1997," said the press
release issued Wednesday by the SONA.
</P>
<P>
"Application forms and the code of procedure for South Asian
Architecture Awards can be downloaded from the relative internet
net site or obtained from Society of Nepalese Architects," the
press release said.
</P>
<P>
The South Asian Architecture Awards for 1997 comprise the South
Asian Architect of the Year Award 1997, the South Asian
Architecture Commendation Awards 1997 and the Great Master's Award
1997, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The Architect of the Year Award is conferred for outstanding
and innovative architectural creation with an award of 100,000
Indian rupees (2,380 U.S. dollars), a citation and a trophy, while
the two commendation awards are presented for notable achievement
in the field of architecture with an award of 50,000 Indian rupees
(1190 dollars), a citation and a trophy.
</P>
<P>
The Great Master's Award is open to both India and the focus
countries and is bestowed for distinguished lifetime contributions
in the sphere of architecture, the press release said, adding that
it carries 100,000 India rupees (2,380 dollars), a citation and a
trophy, the press release said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
