<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 63 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday closed at 2833.04 as
against last close of 2895.84, netting a loss of 62.80 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index dipped by 26.14 points to 1270.62 from
previous close of 1296.76.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted substantially
down at 296.59 and 116.88 compared with previous close of 302.14
and 119.03 respectively.
</P>
<P>
After a smart recovery of about 111 points, equities beat a
hefty retreat, pushing down the Bombay Stock Exchange sensitive
index by 63 points as foreign funds turned net sellers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
