<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Lifts Closure, Curfew on Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Israeli troops Wednesday
lifted the closure and curfew imposed on the West Bank city of
Hebron earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The general closure and curfew were imposed after a
29-year-old Jewish settler was shot dead in Hebron on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio said that on Wednesday morning, the soldiers
removed the roadblocks they had set up around Hebron, allowing
Palestinians to enter or leave the city.
</P>
<P>
About 30,000 Palestinians living in the Israeli-controlled
sector of the city were also allowed to leave their homes.
</P>
<P>
Israel made the decision to lift the closure and curfew after
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) announced on Tuesday that
its security forces have arrested two Palestinians suspected of
murdering the settler.
</P>
<P>
The arrest was a sign of new security cooperation between
Israel and the PNA after a land-for-peace agreement was signed
last Friday in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Israel will hand over 13 percent of the
West Bank to the Palestinians in the second troop redeployment, in
return for the fulfillment of the Palestinian commitments to
fight terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
