<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Declaration At Global Civil Protection Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A declaration to provide
protection for people everywhere in the 21st century was adopted
at the last meeting of the 11th World Conference on Civil
Protection today.
</P>
<P>
It says that protecting and assisting victims of natural and
man-made disasters is a guarantee of basic human rights and that
civil protection systems are the most appropriate way to save
lives, property and the environment, before, during and after
disasters.
</P>
<P>
It also provided a world action plan for developing civil
protection structures, including basic theories on national civil
protection, a framework for international cooperation and mutual
assistance, and management procedural standards in emergency
situations.
</P>
<P>
It emphasized the importance of prevention of disasters and
international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Doje Cering, chairman of the conference and China's Civil
Affairs Minister, said at the closing ceremony that civil
protection has a close relation with world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
