<HEADLINE> Finnish Prime Minister Visits Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Prime Minister Paavo
Lipponen visited the city of Kunshan in the Chinese province of
Jiangsu and discussed the province's economic development and
trade with Finland with Ji Yunshi, Jiangsu's acting governor.
</P>
<P>
Ji said that in the first nine months of this year, they
imported 23 million U.S. dollars worth of goods from Finland.
</P>
<P>
Finland has 12 joint ventures in the province with over 160
million U.S. dollars worth of investment. Ji said he hopes that
Lipponen's visit will help cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen said that friendly political cooperation between the
two countries has laid a good foundation for bilateral economic
cooperation, and that Finnish enterprises view Jiangsu as a base
for business in China, and he attended the opening ceremony of a
Finnish-funded enterprise in the town of Chengbei.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen said that the company, Knoe Elevator, is an important
Finnish enterprise and that Chengbei is an ideal place for
investment, and that project is a model of bilateral economic
cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
