<HEADLINE> Coca-Cola Company Donates to Flood-affected Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Coca-Cola Company today
donated 780,000 yuan (94,000 U.S. dollars) to students whose
schools were affected by the severe Yangtze River flooding this
summer.
</P>
<P>
The money donated to the Hubei Provincial Youth Development
Foundation will help 7,800 students. So far, the soft-drink giant
has given financial assistance to help a total of 30,000
flood-affected students in Heilongjiang, Hunan and Hubei provinces
return to school.
</P>
<P>
Hubei Province in central China was the region hit hardest by the
flooding. The disaster destroyed over 6,700 schools,
affecting about one million students and causing economic losses
of over two billion yuan to schools in Hubei.
</P>
<P>
The Hubei provincial government has already allocated over 44
million yuan to help rebuild the schools. Meanwhile, the Youth
Foundation has raised 17 million yuan to set up 1,000 tent schools
for over 11,000 students.
</P>
<P>
According to a company source, the Coca-Cola Company has given
20 million yuan since 1994 for the construction of 50 primary
schools and 100 libraries in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
