<HEADLINE> Agronomists Suggest Measures for Increasing Incomes of Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Agronomists attending a
seminar which ended here today said that China should make efforts
to increase the incomes of farmers.
</P>
<P>
To do this, China should develop high-quality, high-efficiency
and high-yielding agriculture, increase investment in agriculture,
and speed up the transfer of farm workers to other industries,
said Duan Yingbi, deputy director of the Financial and Economic
Leading Group Office of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural experts noted that the slow increase of income for
farmers has become one of the most challenging problems facing
the rural economy.
</P>
<P>
In the past nine months, the per capita income for farmers
increased by only one percent over the same period last year in
real term.
</P>
<P>
Ye Ying, a Ministry of Agriculture official, also said that
efforts should be made to set up coordinated relations between
industry and agriculture, and between rural and urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Experts agreed that the household contract responsibility
system does not conflict with collective operations and local
governments should do their best to stabilize such a system.
</P>
<P>
Other topics include the development of township enterprises
and small towns, and rural tax and fee-charging reforms. More than
80 agronomists attended the two-day seminar to commemorate the
20th anniversary of the rural reform, sponsored by the Ministry of
Agriculture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
