<HEADLINE> Chinese, New Zealand Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan held talks here today with Don Mckinnon, New Zealand
minister of foreign affairs and trade.
</P>
<P>
In a friendly atmosphere, the two foreign ministers had an
exchange of views on bilateral relations and other regional and
global issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The two sides remarked positively on the growth of the
China-New Zealand relationship.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that bilateral ties have entered a new development
phase thanks to the efforts of both sides, and that the frequent
high-level visits and contacts have given impetus to the growth of
bilateral ties and expanded cooperation in the military,
educational and tourism fields.
</P>
<P>
Mckinnon said that bilateral ties have endured the test of time
and built up an extensive and solid foundation after the formation
of diplomatic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both ministers agreed to continue efforts to strengthen
high-level contacts and expand friendly exchanges and cooperation
in all fields to establish a long-term, stable, friendly and
cooperative relationship toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also agreed to set up a regular
consultation mechanism on regional security issues at the
vice-ministerial level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
