<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Urges U.N. to Improve Performance in Northern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has urged U.N. agencies to
improve their performance in implementing the part of the
oil-for-food program relevant to the northern Kurdish autonomous
region, the Iraqi News Agency INA reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan, said INA,
Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf complained that
despite U.N. promises to improve the performance of its agencies
in northern Iraqi provinces, Iraq had noted "neither a change at
the performance level nor any increase in the implementation ratio."
</P>
<P>
Executive Director of U.N. Humanitarian Program for Iraq Benon
Sevan held meetings with the executive chairmen of the
U.N. agencies in northern Iraq on June 22 till July of 1998 and
promised to take measures to improve the humanitarian situation
there.
</P>
<P>
The letter calls on the U.N. secretary-general to take all
needed measures to urge the U.N. agencies to act "in a way that
would ensure a right, efficient and quick implementation" of the
program.
</P>
<P>
An article carried by the local newspaper Al-Iraq Daily on
Tuesday said "the Kurdish people in the autonomous region have
not received the full ratio of the items contracted for food,
health, electricity, education, drinking water and sanitation
sectors."
</P>
<P>
It added "this fact was confirmed by U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan in his last June report to the U.N. Security
Council."
</P>
<P>
In order to make the oil-for-food deal a success in the
northern autonomous region, the legitimate authority should
exercise its normal role in directly administrating those
provinces as they are indivisible part of unified Iraq, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi central government has lost its actual control
over the northern Kurdish autonomous region since the end of
1991 Gulf War caused by Iraq's invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The Iraq-U.N. oil-for-food program came into force in December
1996 with declared goals of alleviating the sufferings of the
Iraqi people. The U.N. agencies have been assigned to carrying out
the program in the Kurdish autonomous region instead of the Iraqi
central government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
