<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank's New Development Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China's Huaxia Bank announced
today that it has a new development strategy to improve itself in
5 years.
</P>
<P>
At the bank's 6th anniversary ceremony today, its president,
Duan Xiaoxing, said that from 1999 to 2003, Huaxia will continue
reforms as part of the plan, improve the share system in the
commercial bank, and improve its ability to avoid risks.
</P>
<P>
It will also develop new markets and open new businesses and
improve financial services.
</P>
<P>
By 2003, it will have 140 billion yuan in RMB and foreign
exchange deposits and total assets of 200 billion yuan. It will
also have 350 branches.
</P>
<P>
Huaxia was founded in October 1992. In February 1995, it became
China's first commercial bank to issue shares. The bank's 33
shareholders, who are mainly state-owned enterprises, meant a
capital increase to 2.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By September, foreign exchange and RMB deposits amounted to
32.4 billion yuan, assets were 44.6 billion yuan, and it had 20
billion yuan in loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
