<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Slightly Lower Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah closed at
7,550/7,675 rupiah to the U.S. dollar in the Jakarta inter-bank
spot market Wednesday, declining by 275 points compared with
Tuesday's close of 7,275/7,375 rupiah per U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Trading was relatively quiet as players eventually adopted a
wait-and-see attitude, a dealer working for a private bank said.
</P>
<P>
The absence of a driving factor was expected to make trading
become more quiet in the coming days with market players tending
to become more cautious, he added.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah, which hit an eight-month high of 7,150 last
Wednesday, slid back to 7,800 on Thursday and to 7,850 on Friday.
The Indonesian currency strengthened to 7,500/7,700 on Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
