<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Countries Pull Out of Some Events in Bangkok Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cambodia and the DPR Korea had pulled out of men's basketball,
women's basketball and men's hockey, Oman from men's handball and
Bangladesh from men's soccer, handball and volleyball, an
official from the Organizing Committee said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The official said that despite the withdrawals the Games would
still be the largest ever staged.
</P>
<P>
Before the withdrawal, 11,048 athletes and officials from 41
of 43 members of the Olympic Committee of Asia had applied to
take part in the Bangkok Games.
</P>
<P>
November 6 is the deadline for entries. Afghanistan and
Palestine still have not applied to participate.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the Organizing Committee wanted
stricter penalties for member states withdrawing abruptly from
events because the withdrawals would damage the host country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
