<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Peru-Ecuador Peace Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China voiced its hearty
congratulations today to the signing of the Comprehensive and
Ultimate Peace Agreement by Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori
and his Ecuadorian counterpart Jamil Mahuad in Brasilia on October
26.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang in reply to a
reporter's question today said that the signing of the agreement,
which tends to resolve the border dispute between the two
countries, has shown the sincere will and effort of both
governments and peoples to peacefully resolve, through friendly
consultations, problems between countries left to them by history.
</P>
<P>
Tang hailed the signing of the pact as "another example of
appropriate resolution of international disputes," which
contributes positively to the peace and stability of Latin America.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that both peoples will continue to
devote themselves to maintaining and developing good-neighborly
relations to facilitate economic construction and improved living
standards in their countries.  
</P>
