<DOCNO> XIE19981028.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Holds Official Event to Commemorate War Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- An official ceremony was held
here Wednesday to commemorate those who died in the defense of
Hong Kong against the Japanese between 1941 and 1945.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ceremony held at the City Hall Memorial Garden,
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of China, conveyed salute to all those
who died in the defense of Hong Kong on behalf of the Hong Kong
people.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, the first official event organized by the
HKSAR government to mark the war dead after its establishment on
July 1, 1997, a list containing the names of 115 members of the
Hong Kong Independent Battalion of the Dongjiang Column who died
in the defense of Hong Kong between 1941 and 1945 was added to the
Roll of Honor kept in the Memorial Shrine.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the adding of these names to the Roll of Honor
demonstrates an official commendation of the contribution made by
and the brave acts of members of the battalion.
</P>
<P>
A plaque of the Hong Kong Independent Battalion in both Chinese
and English is also displayed in the Memorial Shrine.
</P>
<P>
The battalion was a guerrilla unit which operated in Hong Kong
during the Sino-Japanese War. Most of its members were local
residents, mainly from the "New Territories".
</P>
<P>
The battalion was set up immediately after Hong Kong was
occupied by the Japanese on December 25, 1941.
</P>
<P>
It contributed a lot to the defense of Hong Kong by wiping out
bandits, escorting hundreds of Chinese intellectuals and
well-known figures to the mainland, helping hundreds of officers
and soldiers of the allied forces and foreign friends to escape
from the control of the Japanese.
</P>
<P>
In fact, after the surrender of the British forces in Hong Kong
to the Japanese, the battalion was the only force to fight against
the Japanese during that period. It withdrew from Hong Kong after
the victory in the war.
</P>
<P>
There were some 1,000 members in the battalion and some 400 of
them are still alive with half of them living in the mainland and
another half residing in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, the chief executive laid a wreath at the
shrine.
</P>
<P>
Senior government officials, representatives of the Judiciary
of the SAR, representatives of the Legislative Council of the SAR,
Hong Kong members of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, Hong Kong deputies to
the National People's Conference were present at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Among others who attended the ceremony were representatives of
Central People's Government organizations in Hong Kong,
representatives of foreign consuls in Hong Kong, relevant members
of the Consular Corps, community leaders and representatives of
war veteran groups and related community organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981028.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
