parties agreed to fresh elections in 18 months to resolve a
bloody dispute over national polls in May.
</P>
<P>
Opposition parties claimed that the May elections were rigged
in favor of the ruling Lesotho Congress for Democracy, which won
79 of the 80 seats in the parliament of the tiny landlocked
country. 
