<HEADLINE> Philippine Army Ordered to Check Existence of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada Wednesday ordered Armed Forces Chief of Staff Joselin
Nazareno to check the existence of a combat group allegedly using
the name of "Malacanang" (presidential palace) in terrorizing
Muslims in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Jerry Barican told reporters here
Wednesday afternoon that the claim that Malacanang is involved in
any way is "simply ridiculous and malicious."
</P>
