<HEADLINE> Davies Resigns as Welsh Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Welsh Secretary Ron
Davies resigned Tuesday for befriending a male stranger on Clapham
Common who robbed him at knife-point.
</P>
<P>
In a resignation to Prime Minister Tony Blair, Davies said he
had been guilty of a "serious lapse of judgement."
</P>
<P>
Pressure is mounting for him to abandon his position as the
Labor party leader in Welsh.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to hold meetings with party officials over the
next few days and travel back to his constituency later this week
to discuss his political future with local party members.
</P>
<P>
Government ministers are attempting to play down the
embarrassment and mystery over why he resigned as Welsh Secretary
so suddenly.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister's official spokesman said that Davies had
been interviewed by the police as a "victim" of a crime.
</P>
<P>
However, observers here believe that the incident was bound to
cause embarrassment as areas of Clapham Common are well known as a
meeting place for homosexuals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
