<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15 Nigerians Burnt to Death in Oil Tanker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people have been burnt
to death and more than 30 injured in a petrol tanker incident in
Ibadan, capital of Oyo State in southwest Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The Punch newspaper quoted eyewitnesses as saying that a
fully-loaded petrol tanker lost control at the Ojoo round-about
and somersaulted as it was maneuvering the sharp junction around
4.00 p.m. (local time) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This resulted in instant spillage of fuel all over the road
and along nearby buildings and shops.
</P>
<P>
Instead of scampering for safety, people in the area rushed to
the scene to collect the petroleum.
</P>
<P>
As they were scooping the petrol, the spillage caught fire and
the ensuing explosion engulfed the area where more than 20 houses
including three buildings were razed to the ground.
</P>
<P>
Only a year ago, the same Ojoo road junction witnessed a
similar disaster in which about 22 people were killed when a fuel
tanker lost control and somersaulted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
