<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Extends Run-Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
surge up on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday on talks of more cuts
in interest rates by local banks and soon-to-be unveiling of
corporate reconstructurings.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 26.62 points to
end at 1,180.22 points in active trading.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover rose to 489.11 million units worth 573.06
million Singapore dollars (353.30 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
edged out losers by 239 to 58 with 122 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Summit topped the active chart with a turnover of 34.32 million
units. Ho Pro was the second most heavily traded stock on the
exchange with a turnover of 28.36 million shares. Wing T was next
with 22.44 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the top gainers of the day as it ran up two
Singapore dollars to 20.80 Singapore dollars at close. Ge Life
rose by 75 cents to finish at 8.90 Singapore dollars. SIA F went
up 40 cents to end at 10.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH XE led the descent of the day with a drop
of 20 cents to close at 14.40 Singapore dollars. Transmarco
retreated 13 cents to close at 2.95 Singapore dollars. Asean
inched 10 cents lower to end at 5.30 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Despite the market's continued ascent, dealers noted caution is
building as valuation has been over-stretched.  
</P>
</TEXT>
