<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Zaman (Time):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkey's National Security Council decided Tuesday to
monitor Syria's compliance with the recent agreement with Turkey
concerning Damascus' promise to stop supporting the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
Turkish and Syrian officials reached an agreement last week in
which Syria pledged to ban PKK activities on its territory and in
the Damascus-controlled Bekka Valley.
</P>
<P>
Cumhuriyet (Republic):
</P>
<P>
-- Speaking at a weekly press briefing Tuesday, Turkish
Foreign Ministry deputy spokesman Sermet Atcanli said that Turkey
is awaiting response from Russia regarding the extradition of the
PKK leader, Abdullah Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
Turkish intelligence authorities have confirmed that Ocalan is
in Russia now.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- A high-level South Korean business delegation is contacting
Turkish business circles in Ankara in an effort to further promote
South Korean-Turkish economic ties.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from over 20 leading South Korean companies
will discuss with Turkish business leaders cooperation issues in
the fields of nuclear energy, steel, electronics, shipbuilding,
construction, etc. 
</P>
