<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Ternate in Indonesia's Maluku Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on
the Richter scale struck Ternate city in Indonesia's Maluku
province Wednesday, according to the Jakarta evening paper Suara
Pembaruan.
</P>
<P>
The quake hit the city at 04:16 local time, with its epicenter
traced at 399 kilometers east of Bitung city in North Sulawesi
province and 100 kilometers beneath the earth's surface.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report on casualty or damage from the
quake. 
</P>
