<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Wednesday as investors remained
cautious and more inclined to stay on the sideline.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 5.47
points to 410.49, the all-share Emas Index shed 1.10 points to
107.10, the Industrial Index lost 6.33 points to 797.88 and the
Second Board dropped 0.39 of a point to 99.35.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 353 to 166 while 172 counters were
unchanged, 227 untraded and 35 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased slightly to 119.030 million shares
valued at 217.468 million ringgit (57.228 million U.S. dollars)
from Tuesday's 114.711 million shares valued at 203.399 million
ringgit (53.526 million U.S. dollars)
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover rose to 110.316 million shares valued
at 204.683 million ringgit (53.863 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 107.487 million shares valued at 191.842 million ringgit
(50.484 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board volume increased to 8.714 million shares
valued at 12.785 million ringgit (3.364 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 7.224 million shares valued at 11.557 million ringgit
(3.041 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market transactions fell to 4.819 million shares valued at
8.348 million ringgit (2.196 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's
14.291 million shares valued at 27.081 million ringgit (7.126
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
One counter -- Comsa Farms was listed on the second board in
the day, which finished the day at 1.28 ringgit, the same price as
its debut, which is eight sen higher than the initial public
offering price of 1.20 ringgit.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products contributed 5.636
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
12.579 million shares, construction 13.488 million shares,
trade/services 31.544 million shares, infrastructure 659,000
shares, finance 16.114 million shares, hotels 715,000 shares,
properties 15.131 million shares, plantation 4.056 million shares,
mining 385,000 shares, trusts 96,000 shares, closed/fund 25,000
shares and loans 9.888 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
