<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 09:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Ends Visit to Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat wrapped up Wednesday a visit to Saudi Arabia during
which he briefed the Saudi leaders on the new Palestinian-Israeli
peace agreement, the Kuwait News Agency (Kuna) reported.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who arrived in Riyadh Monday, met separately with
Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz and Second Deputy Prime Minister,
Minister of Defense and Aviation Prince Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz on
the accord he signed in Washington last Friday with Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Ambassador Mustafa Deeb told Kuna that Arafat
briefed the Saudi leaders of details of the Palestinian-Israeli
negotiations at Wye Plantation, Maryland, the U.S..
</P>
<P>
King Fahd was also briefed of the tactics used by the Israelis
to delay the agreement, Deeb said.
</P>
<P>
Mediation efforts employed by U.S. President Bill Clinton in
helping strike the deal was also briefed, Deeb added.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting with Arafat, King Fahd expressed the hope
that the deal between Israelis and Palestinians would contribute
to the moving forward of the Syrian-Israeli and the
Lebanese-Israeli tracks of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi monarch assured Arafat that Saudi Arabia will be
firmly behind the Palestinian cause.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is currently on a Gulf tour which also includes Qatar
and the United Arab Emirates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
