<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hijacked Chinese Civilian Plane Returns to Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese civilian plane that
was hijacked to Taiwan this morning took off from the Taipei
International Airport at around 18:10 hours today (Beijing Time)
on its way back to the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
The hijacked plane, B2949, a Boeing 737 of Air China, is flying
to Xiamen of southeast China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
It was hijacked on a flight from Beijing to the southwestern
Chinese city of Kunming, with 95 passengers aboard, including 20
overseas passengers and a crew of nine.
</P>
<P>
The plane safely landed in the Taipei International Airport at
11:17 hours today with no injuries reported, sources added.
</P>
<P>
The suspect hijackers are the captain of the plane Yuan Bin and
his wife.  
</P>
</TEXT>
