<HEADLINE> Fireworks Producer Establishes Joint Venture in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China's major fireworks
producer recently established a joint venture in Brazil, according
to the recent issue of the paper International Business News.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, the first of its kind, was established by
the Jiangsu Jianhu Fireworks Co., and it will produce 2,000 tons
of fireworks valued at 4.5 million U.S. dollars annually. The
company expects annual profits to hit 1.35 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Jianhu company with 33 factories produces more than 2,000
kinds of fireworks and they are exported to more than 20 countries
and regions in Europe, America, Southeast Asia and Africa.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's 15 fireworks companies lack the production scale and
technology needed to meet domestic demand during during festivals.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's annual demand for fireworks stands at 100,000 tons.
</P>
