<HEADLINE> Beijing Initiates High-Tech Agricultural Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech agricultural
development zone is being constructed in Beijing's Haidian
District at a cost of 500 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The development zone, located in Liaogong Village in Haidian
District's Sijiqing Township, will develop high technologies such
as biological and cultivation technologies and environmental
control, improve crop varieties to raise grain output, and develop
agriculture-related industries.
</P>
<P>
Thus far, the zone has built a 200-square-meter bio-technology
laboratory, an 800-square-meter workshop for cultivating flowers
and a 2.6-hectare greenhouse for cultivating fruit trees.
</P>
<P>
The zone has also set up a laboratory for producing animal
embryos and conducting animal gene research.
</P>
<P>
The zone also has a center for treating endangered wild and
aquatic animal species such as giant salamanders and Chinese
sturgeon.  
</P>
