<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Fall in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices fell for the fourth
consecutive trading day in Tokyo Wednesday on worries over poor
midterm corporate earnings.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 304.61 points, or 2.20
percent, from Tuesday's close at 13,516.07.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 14.37 points or 1.38 percent to
1,028.61.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section remained low at about 306 million
shares, down from 350.01 million shares Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ishikawa Seisakusho, a textile machine maker, was the day's
most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei index surged at the start, gaining 100 points on
what traders said was due to a huge one-time purchase of various
shares by an unspecified brokerage.
</P>
<P>
But the advance evaporated as investors jettisoned shares of
major firms unveiling dismal financial figures for the
April-September fiscal half-year, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,344 issues listed on the First Section, losers
outnumbered gainers by 740 to 337, with 187 issues unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
