related documents, which were signed in the wake of the talks
between Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski and his visiting
Moldovan counterpart Kirillovich Luchinsky, the two countries will
enhance cooperation on military technology and industry. Poland
will also help Moldova train military officers.
(Poland-Moldova-Military Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- The North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) Tuesday
ended its large-scale military exercise aimed at curbing and
resolving a real crisis in the Balkan area.
</P>
<P>
Commander-in-chief of Allied Forces of Southern Europe James
Ellis said that the exercise, code-named Dynamic Mix 98, tested
the capability of NATO forces handling two separate crises
simultaneously and strengthened coordination among different
combatant arms. More than 5,000 military personnel from 11 NATO
countries participated in the four-week long exercise conducted
simultaneously in Italy, Greece and Turkey. (NATO-Military
Exercises) 
</P>
