<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 10 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Tuesday killed 10 Tamil rebels in the Northern province, according
to military spokesman here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops confronted a group
of Tamil rebels and engaged them with small arms at Vannivi
Lankulam area Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The troops killed at least three rebels in the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The same day evening at southwest of Paranthan, troops on a
limited operation engaged and destroyed a few terrorist bunkers
with the support of armor, killing five rebels, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident at Paranthan Tuesday morning, government
troops sniped and killed two Tamil rebels, Dewage added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
island country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
