<HEADLINE> Bonds Issue for Fujian International Airport Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Bonds worth 232 million yuan for
additional construction at Changle International Airport in
Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian Province, were put on
public sale today.
</P>
<P>
The marketing of the bonds, targeted at corporate,
institutional and private investors, has won approval from the
Chinese State Development Planning Commission and People's Bank of
China Fujian Branch, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
The bonds have a term of three years and an annual interest
rate of 6.93 percent. The bond sale will last for one month.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Chengxin Securities Evaluation Co. Ltd.,
the credibility of the bonds is classified as A grade.
</P>
<P>
The well-equipped Changle International Airport, at a cost of
2.8 billion yuan, is the first large international airport in
China built by a local government with self-raised funds. It has
been operating well since it was completed and put into service in
June 1997, and is considered to have great development potential.
</P>
<P>
The money raised from the sale of these bonds will be fully
used to finance finishing touches to the airport.  
</P>
