<HEADLINE> FUNCINPEC, CPP Should Join Hands Without Delay, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The FUNCINPEC and the
Cambodian People's Party (CPP) should join hands without further
delay to sit down to resolve the basic problems of sharing power
for the sake of the country and the people, Chea Sim, president of
the ruling CPP, appealed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released by his cabinet Wednesday, Chea Sim
said, "The two parties are the key holders to the current
political deadlock and the nucleus of national reconciliation,
political stability and national development."
</P>
<P>
"So we must sit down at the negotiation table and resolve the
basic problems of sharing power, of operating the National
Assembly and of distributing responsibilities in the new royal
coalition government," he added.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement in response to the recent criticisms by
certain politicians, political parties, local and international
news media and certain rights organizations, who accused the CPP's
refusal to make concession to the opposition.
</P>
<P>
Chea Sim asserted the election was conducted within the
framework of the constitution, the electoral law, the party law
and other laws in force in the nation, and also the election had
the Constitutional Council and local and international observer
teams as arbitrator, so the results of the election reflected the
will of the people.
</P>
<P>
"The CPP obviously cannot make any legal concession in order to
alter the results," he reiterated. "The July 26 election gave the
CPP 64 seats, the FUNCINPEC 43 seats, and the Sam Rainsy Party
(SRP) 15 seats. This was the final result. Even if more demands
were filed, or any kind of concession was made by the CPP, still
there would have no influence to exert any change."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chea Sim said the CPP is prepared to make
appropriate concession to the FUNCINPEC, a partner in the royal
coalition government.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the CPP nurses no ambition for exclusive power,
but wants to see the establishment of a coalition government.
</P>
<P>
He said that the dark shadow of the past must be erased. This
shadow must be replaced by the new page of cooperation and
understanding based on the constitution and other laws and the
advancement of the national interests.
</P>
<P>
The FUNCINPEC and the CPP should face realities by responding
in concrete action to the trust and confidence of the people who
have elected them to public offices and lead the nation into the
21st century, Chea Sim said.
</P>
<P>
So far, the two opposition political parties, the FUNCINPEC and
the SRP, and their leaders Prince Ranariddh and Sam Rainsy still
rejected to join the government, insisting the CPP won the
election through fraud and intimidation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
