<HEADLINE> Tibet Punishes Poachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen Tibetan poachers from
Ngari Prefecture in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region were
recently fined and sentenced to prison.
</P>
<P>
The convicted criminals killed more than 500 Tibetan antelope
and illegally purchased 212 hides during January and February this
year.
</P>
<P>
The local people's court rendered sentences ranging from three
to 13 years and imposed fines of between 700-15,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghai-Tibet Plateau is the natural habitat of rare
Tibetan antelope, with the estimated worldwide population of the
species standing at 100,000. 
</P>
