<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pudong New Area Exports More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area of
Shanghai reported a total export of commodities worth 3.413
billion U.S. dollars from January to September, up 19 percent over
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Sources at a recent meeting on Pudong's foreign trade said that
the New Area's exports in the first three quarter of this year
made up 28 percent of Shanghai's total, compared with 19.8 percent
in 1994 and 26 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's exports are expected to continue to climb in the
coming months despite the adverse impact of the Asian financial
crisis, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade specialists attribute Pudong's growing exports to
a strong contingent of foreign trade teams, the strategy of
expanding diversified export markets, and efforts to improve the
technological content of export commodities and promote
technological and service trades in addition to trade in kind.
</P>
<P>
Pudong is now home to over 300 professional foreign trade
companies, more than 100 manufacturing enterprises with autonomy
to import and export independently, and more than 5,000
overseas-financed businesses. It also has three overseas-backed
foreign trade companies and 100 foreign-trade subsidiaries opened
by other Chinese foreign-trade companies outside Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Since the Asian financial crisis began in July last year,
Pudong has redoubled efforts to export to Japan and maintain its
export share to Europe and the United States while making
painstaking efforts to explore new markets in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Pudong now exports more than 20 categories of commodities with
30,000 specifications to 130 countries and regions, and has an
in-place worldwide export network.  
</P>
</TEXT>
