<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Bank: S.Korean Economy to Recover Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 28 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's economy will begin
a slow recovery next year with improvement in consumption and
investment, the Bank of Korea said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Although the global economic growth will slow down due to the
Asian economic crisis, sluggish economic growth in the United
States and the gradual weakening of Japan's yen against the
greenback in 1999, South Korea's economy will recover slowly from
next year, said the bank in a report to the National Assembly, or
parliament.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said once the government-sponsored economic
reforms come to an end next year, consumption and investment will
pick up, credit crunch will be eased gradually and the whole
economy will improve.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank said, South Korea will maintain a surplus
in its current account balance for a while but the black figures
will decline as exports will continue slow-paced in 1999.
</P>
<P>
In the report, the central bank also said the inflation rate of
this year will be near eight percent while consumer prices will
rise eight percent by the end of this year, close to the initial
forecast of nine percent because of stabilized foreign exchange
rate and prices.
</P>
<P>
Since being gripped by the financial crisis caused by corporate
bankruptcies and bad loans of financial institutions late last
year, South Korea's economy has plunged into a deep recession as
the gross domestic product and domestic consumption contracted
sharply in the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The country's economy slumped 6.4 percent in the first half of
this year while the GNP contracted five percent and 7.6 percent in
the first and second quarters respectively, the worst setback
after the 1950-53 Korean War.
</P>
<P>
Economists predicted that the economy will deteriorate in the
second half of this year as there is no sign of improvement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981028.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
