<HEADLINE> 31 Injured in Student Soccer Fans Brawl in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The rampaging crowd also vandalized the Mandala Krida Stadium,
the venue of the match pitting teams from the Indonesian Islamic
University and Janabadra University.
</P>
<P>
They burned a section reserved for the press, broke glass
doors leading to the VIP room and destroyed a mini studio
belonging to the state radio station RRI, the Jakarta Post
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted witnesses as saying that the animosity was
noticeable before the semifinal match of the tournament held by
Janabadra University was about to begin. Students of the two
local private universities started to throw objects at each
other, but calmed down after representatives of the two sides met
and agreed to hold a peaceful game.
</P>
<P>
But the truce lasted only 90 minutes. Shortly after referee
Hendro Kardiono blew the final whistle, Janabadra University
supporters rushed over to where the opposition supporters were
celebrating after the game was decided 1-0 by a controversial
penalty.
</P>
<P>
The penalty decision prompted protests from the Janabadra
players, but Hendro stood his ground.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday evening, tension still gripped the main campuses of
the two university. Dozens of students from each university were
on alert, with some arming themselves with iron bars.
</P>
<P>
Fearing revenge by the Indonesian Islamic University students,
dozens of police blockade the Janabadra University compound
throughout the day on Tuesday. But no fresh clashes were
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
