<HEADLINE> Moat Plan Beautifies Ancient Wall in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- One thousand soldiers are
working day and night to clean the moat around the ancient city
wall in Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province,
according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The aim of the comprehensive municipal project is to beautify
the 14.6-km-long moat.
</P>
<P>
The wall is considered one of China's best-preserved
relics. People around the world consider the wall as the symbol of
the city's history. It was renovated in 1983.
</P>
<P>
However, the scenery has been spoiled in recent years by
pollution, prompting citizens' complaints.
</P>
<P>
The local government allocated 84.7 million yuan (10.2 million
U.S. dollars) to remove the silt deposits and cover the river bed
with stones.
</P>
<P>
"We invited soldiers to ensure quicker, and better,
construction," said Wang Ge, secretary of the city government's
construction bureau. 
</P>
