<HEADLINE> Dentist Team Offers Health Care in Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen years ago, a team of
10 dentists went to poverty-stricken villages in the mountains of
Wuyi County in east China's Zhejiang Province to perform medical
examinations as well as necessary interventions.
</P>
<P>
They also spread knowledge on oral health among children and
the young people.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese, especially those from remote areas, rarely know know
to protect their teeth," said He Dewen, a dentist and leader of
the team, quoted by the China Daily today.
</P>
<P>
He is also director of the Center of Oral Health in the county.
</P>
<P>
The activity gave inspiration to a one-year national campaign
to improve oral health in remote areas throughout China.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, named after the famous Long March, was initiated
jointly by the Ministry of Health, and the National Committee for
Oral Health in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
From September last year to this October, the campaign
organized six groups of experts to help the poorest regions in 12
provinces across China. The campaign has benefited millions of
people living in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
More than 130 pieces of dental care equipment has been
delivered to these counties for free, said Bian Jinyou,
vice-director of the National Committee for Oral Health.
</P>
<P>
The latest survey shows that over 85 percent of the population
in the targeted counties is now aware of the importance and basic
methods of dental care.  
</P>
</TEXT>
