<HEADLINE> Two Feared Dead in Furniture Store Blaze in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Two people were feared dead
Tuesday evening in a major fire in one of Beijing's largest
furniture and decorating materials markets, reports today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
"Two men entered the furniture hall when the fire began to
burn, but we must fear the worst since they have not yet
reemerged," said an official with Juran Zhijia (Comfortable Home)
Furniture City, located on the Fourth Ring Road in Chaoyang
District, quoted by the paper.
</P>
<P>
A policeman confirmed that at least one person had died.
</P>
<P>
The devastating blaze in the furniture market, the second
largest after the fire that gutted Yuquanying Furniture City in
May this year, started at 7:20 pm and was eventually put out at
10:30 pm, according to a fireman.
</P>
<P>
Half of the first and second floors were destroyed by the fire.
</P>
<P>
Policemen gave no indication of the cause of the fire, saying
it was under investigation. But, Sheng Wenlian, a vendor in the
hall, said the probable cause was electric welding.
</P>
<P>
Sheng said her store inside the hall was destroyed in the
blaze, resulting in losses of nearly 100,000 yuan (12,048 US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
