<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Funding for Wild Life Protection in Sri </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) has approved a funding of 2.5 billion U.S. dollars for a
national conservation program to protect wild life in Sri Lanka,
according to Wildlife Department sources here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seven year program to be launched by the Wildlife
Department aims at promoting conservation activities through the
involvement of communities living in the vicinity of the country's
wild life parks and sanctuaries, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A special feature of the program is the introduction of
projects to uplift the living standards of people in these
vicinities and the launching of various programs to increase their
incomes, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
This would eliminate their dependence on resources within the
parks and reduce threats posed to the wild life in these parks and
 sanctuaries, said the sources, adding that projects will also be
identified depending on the various need of these communities.
</P>
</TEXT>
