<HEADLINE> Poland, Moldova Signs Agreements on Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Poland and Moldova Tuesday
signed three agreements on cooperation in military technology and
regional cooperation, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Poland and Moldova military technology cooperation
agreement and two related documents were signed in the wake of the
talks betweent Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski and
visiting Moldovan President Kirillovich Luchinsky.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreements, the two countries will enhance
cooperations in military technology and industry. Poland will help
Moldova train military officers.
</P>
<P>
Luchinsky is on the first day of a two-day official visit at
the invitation of Kwasniewski.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents discussed the impact of the Russian
financial crisis, regional cooperation and situation in the
Pridnestr River area.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski said Poland would do its best to seek a peaceful
settlement of the conflicts in the Pridnestr River area.
</P>
<P>
Luchinsky suggested the establishment of a "new
close-cooperation area" with Poland, Ukraine, and Romania to solve
the problems in the conflict area.
</P>
<P>
Conflicts broke out between the Moldovan government and the
authorities in the Pridnestr River area following their
declaration of independence in September 1990.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of Moldova, Russia, Ukraine and Poland
will meet in Kiev in November to look for a solution to the
conflicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
