<HEADLINE> NATO Ends Large-scale Military Exercise in Balkan Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) Tuesday ended its large-scale military
exercise aimed at curbing and resolving a real crisis in the
Balkan area.
</P>
<P>
Commander-in-chief of Allied Forces of Southern Europe James
Ellis said that the exercise, codenamed Dynamic Mix 98, tested the
capability of NATO forces handling two separate crises
simultaneously and strengthened coordination among different
combatant arms.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 military personnel from 11 NATO countries'
navy, army, amphibious and air forces took part in the four-week
long exercise conducted simultaneously in Italy, Greece and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Also participating in the exercises were 62 warships and 170
airplanes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
