<HEADLINE> Chinese Chief of General-Staff Arrives in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- General Fu Quanyou, chief of
the general-staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA)
said Tuesday he believed his current visit to Brazil will improve
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued after he arrived in Sao Paulo for
a five-day visit, General Fu said the friendly cooperation between
China and Brazil has made great progress in various fields since
the two countries established relations 24 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also established a strategic
partnership, he said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
He said that his aim of the visit is to increase understanding
and deepen friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Fu is expected to meet with Brazilian president Fernando
Henrique Cardoso and his Brazilian counterpart General Benedito
Leonel.
</P>
<P>
He will also meet with Brazil's army, navy and air force
commanders and the president's office secretary for strategic
affairs.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Fu will tour military barracks in the cities
of Sao Paulo, Brasilia and Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the last leg of his Latin American tour which also
took him to Peru, Argentina and Uruguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
