<HEADLINE> Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone Spurs Shanghai Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone,
the first zone of its kind in China's Shanghai, has achieved rapid
growth over the past five years and has contributed greatly to
promoting the municipality's export volume.
</P>
<P>
Waigaoqiao's export volume grew by 46 percent annually during
the period, with exports for the first nine months of this year
hitting 695 million US dollars, up 41 percent.
</P>
<P>
A local official attributed the achievements to the zone's
preferential tariff policies which have attracted multinational
companies such as Intel, Hewlett Packard, Philips and JVC. The
zone's improved infrastructure system and expanded services have
attracted a number of new enterprises, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-US General Motors Plant in the New Pudong Area has
attracted a number of foreign spare parts manufacturers which
account for a large portion of the zone's export volume.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in the zone have entered markets across the world,
and products from the zone are currently sold in 33 countries and
regions. The zone's total export volume has jumped to 50 million
US dollars this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
