<HEADLINE> Belarussian Leaders Want Enhanced Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MINSK, October 27 (Xinhua) -- With Sino-Belarus relations
developing smoothly and with a broad prospect ahead, Belarus hopes
to further enhance mutually beneficiary cooperation with China,
Belarussian parliamentary leaders said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Pavel Shipuk, chairman
of the National Assembly of Belarussian House of Republics (Upper
House), said China is a great country and Belarus has all along
attached great importance to developing relations with it.
</P>
<P>
Since their establishment of diplomatic ties in 1992, he said,
the two countries have pushed forward their relations steadily.
</P>
<P>
In recently years, the two have increased high-level exchanges
and a series of documents signed by their leaders are now yielding
fruits, he said.
</P>
<P>
Anatoly Malofeyev, speaker of the National Assembly of
Belarussian House of Representatives (Lower House), said the two
countries share identical views in major international issues and
have always supported each other in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Since China is certain to play an important role in the 21st
century, it is of great importance for Belarus to develop
relations with China, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said the current level of business transaction
between the two countries stays low, amounting to only three
percent of Belarus' total foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Saying the two countries are in good position to cooperate and
have huge potential to tap, Malofeyev hopes both sides can further
enhance cooperation in machinery making, science and technology
and military production. He welcomed Chinese entrepreneurs to
invest in Belarus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
