<HEADLINE> Large Amount of Stimulant Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
99 brands of 2.89 million stimulant drug tablets weighing 260.1
kilograms in the country's northern Shan state last month, the
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was made by a combined team of regional
intelligence unit, police and the customs who searched a car at
the Sint-in checkpoint near Lashio township on September 19.
</P>
<P>
The local police station has taken action against two people in
connection with the case under Myanmar's Narcotic Drug and
Psychotropic Substances Law, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last month, the authorities also seized more than one
million stimulant drug tablets in Kengtung of the same state and
took action against five people involved in the trafficking.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the Myanmar authorities
confiscated nearly 9 million stimulant drug tablets in the first
nine months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
