<HEADLINE> Power Project Proceeds Smoothly in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Qingjiang River, one of the
tributaries of the Yangtze River in the middle reaches, was dammed
on Monday to facilitate second stage construction of the Gaobazhou
Hydropower Station.
</P>
<P>
Gaobazhou, the last power station along the main channel of the
Qingjiang River in central China's Hubei Province, has a designed
installed capacity of 252,000 kw and will produce 898 million kwh
of electricity annually when fully operational in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
First phase construction included the construction of a
cofferdam, a dam on one bank, a power plant and a flood discharge
tunnel. The second phase will focus on the construction of a dam
on the other side of the river and a ship lock.
</P>
<P>
The power plant will be constructed at a cost of 3.7 billion
yuan. The first generating unit is scheduled to go online at the
end of this month and the entire project will be completed in the
year 2002.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
