<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Floods Honduras As Hurricane Nears </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Hurricane Mitch sent heavy
rain on Honduras' northern Atlantic coast as it was traveling 150
kilometers away toward Mexico's Yucatan peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecaster German Blanco said on Tuesday that clouds
caused by the hurricane would remain over the country for the next
48 hours.
</P>
<P>
National emergency authorities said that at least 25 fishermen
were missing at sea, but did not report more victims despite
extensive floodings in northern rivers.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people were evacuated from the coast before the
storm arrived, and the government has sent more than 2.5 tons of
food, clothes, medicines and other staples to be distributed to
the refugees.
</P>
<P>
Mitch is currently going towards Mexico at a speed 13
kilometers per hour, moving away from the Atlantic and Caribbean
coasts.
</P>
<P>
Forecasters predicted, however, that it could affect several
islands off the Honduran coast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
