<HEADLINE> Philippine Government to Beef Up Bank Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government may
draw 2 billion U.S. dollars from the 30 billion dollar Miyazawa
plan to beef up bank capital.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Bulletin newspaper reported Wednesday that the
government will use the loan to infuse additional capital in the
state-owned Philippine National Bank (PNB), Land Bank of the
Philippines and the Development Bank of the Philippines (DBP).
</P>
<P>
Japanese Finance Minister Kiichi Miyazawa announced in
Washington early this month the 30 billion dollar allocation to
the economies severely hit by the Asian financial crisis to help
them recover fast.
</P>
<P>
"We plan to use some of the proceeds of the loan as capital
enhancement for Land Bank, DBP and PNB," Finance Secretary Edgardo
Espiritu said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But he said that the amount of capital infusion to the three
government financial institutions is still under study. 
</P>
